1
00:00:00,967 --> 00:00:04,767
<i>If your families won't
give me what I need,</i>

2
00:00:04,767 --> 00:00:06,367
<i>then I'll approach
another family.</i>

3
00:00:06,367 --> 00:00:07,367
<i>- No!
- No!</i>

4
00:00:07,367 --> 00:00:09,367
<i> They're just close, dear.</i>

5
00:00:09,367 --> 00:00:11,200
<i> They're not that far.</i>

6
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,700
- [SARI SCREAMING]
- [SANDRO GROANING IN PAIN]

7
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:17,767
<i>Sir, the Sandro you're looking
for is just here at Hotel 88.</i>

8
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,767
<i> Sir, he's not leaving.</i>

9
00:00:19,767 --> 00:00:21,767
- [MUFFLED GROAN]
<i> - Edward?</i>

10
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:23,367
<i> Edward!</i>

11
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>Give me your map if
you want your son to live.</i>

12
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:29,600
<i> I already have this.</i>

13
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,033
<i> All of you are fooling me!</i>

14
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:33,200
<i> It's with the Almazans.</i>

15
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,200
<i>If it's not with
Michael's children,</i>

16
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:36,633
<i>it's definitely
with the Almazans.</i>

17
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,467
<i> Luna, that's the last piece.</i>

18
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,067
<i> You found it.</i>

19
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:41,633
<i>Let's give this to Kiko.
They need it.</i>

20
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>- Just go!
- Please, give me the map!</i>

21
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,700
<i>- Mom!
- Where's the map?</i>

22
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,367
<i>- Give me the map!
- M-map?</i>

23
00:00:47,367 --> 00:00:49,200
<i>- Uncle...
- We don't have it!</i>

24
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:52,067
- Stop, Uncle!
- I know you have it!

25
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,533
I know you have it.

26
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:56,533
Please just give it to me.
I need the map.

27
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:58,367
Just give it.
Give it to me.

28
00:00:58,367 --> 00:01:02,533
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

29
00:01:02,533 --> 00:01:04,333
We'll give it to you.

30
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:06,733
Just don't hurt Mom.

31
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,400
Don't mess with me.

32
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,567
Go.

33
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:14,467
Uncle, put that down.
Don't hurt our mom.

34
00:01:14,467 --> 00:01:15,633
Please, please.

35
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:18,633
Luna, Jade, I don't want
to hurt your mother.

36
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:20,800
Frida, I don't want to hurt you.

37
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:23,367
I just need the map. That's all.

38
00:01:23,367 --> 00:01:24,767
- Just the map.
- [JADE] Uncle...

39
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:26,367
Uncle, please.

40
00:01:26,367 --> 00:01:28,367
Uncle, please stop.
Don't do that.

41
00:01:28,367 --> 00:01:29,733
This is what you want, right?

42
00:01:30,367 --> 00:01:31,500
Take it!

43
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:33,367
[JUSTIN] Let go of my mom.

44
00:01:33,367 --> 00:01:34,767
[FRIDA WHIMPERS]

45
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:37,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

46
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:40,733
[FRIDA WHIMPERING]

47
00:01:42,633 --> 00:01:44,200
You won't follow me behind.

48
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:46,400
Do not call the police!

49
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,567
I'm sorry.

50
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:49,167
I'm sorry this had to happen.

51
00:01:49,167 --> 00:01:50,300
[KNIFE CLINKS]

52
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:53,167
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

53
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:56,300
- Are you all right, Mom?
- Yes, I'm okay.

54
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:59,767
Justin, what was the map
that you gave him?

55
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,800
Sandro's map.

56
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:09,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

57
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:10,467
You found it?

58
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,733
Luna found it.

59
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:14,500
If so...

60
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:17,733
What else are you waiting for?
You have to go to the hotel.

61
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:19,233
They're looking for this!

62
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:20,633
But you'll be alone here.

63
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:22,400
- I'll be okay.
- Mom.

64
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,433
I will call the police.

65
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:25,633
But, Mom, Uncle Andy said
that we shouldn't--

66
00:02:25,633 --> 00:02:27,633
He can't do anything about it.

67
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:29,233
You should get going.

68
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:30,867
Kiko needs someone
to be with him.

69
00:02:30,867 --> 00:02:32,800
- We can't leave you.
- What about you, Mom?

70
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,800
I'll be okay. Go, go!

71
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,767
You have to go.

72
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,400
You have to go.

73
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,767
[FRIDA] Okay, go. Be careful.

74
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,767
- Be careful.
- We'll return quickly.

75
00:02:46,767 --> 00:02:49,367
- Call us, Mom.
- Please, Mom!

76
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:52,400
- Hurry up! Go, go, go.
- Mom...

77
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,567
- Stay in your room, Mom.
- I will. Go, go!

78
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:57,167
[JADE] Let's hurry up so
we can return to Mom quickly.

79
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:59,300
Mom, go back to your room!

80
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:09,367
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:31,367
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:53,367
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:08,833
[EDWARD MUFFLED GROAN]

84
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:15,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

85
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:18,367
[ANDY] Don't worry, bud.

86
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,400
I'm already here. Don't worry.

87
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,533
Dad...

88
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:32,433
[ANDY] There, you've completed
the map now.

89
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,800
We can divide the treasure now.

90
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:38,667
You're still the same bastard,
Arellano.

91
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,633
I'm not an idiot!

92
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:43,567
This map is from my house.

93
00:04:43,567 --> 00:04:45,933
This is my missing map!

94
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:49,433
No! That's what Justin gave me.

95
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:51,800
That's the only map that
the Almazans have!

96
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:54,267
You didn't go to
the Almazan residence.

97
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:55,800
I went there!

98
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,500
[SANDRO] You've had
my map for a long time!

99
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:02,633
And if you had it,
then you got it from my son!

100
00:05:02,667 --> 00:05:05,067
You're the one who
really killed my son!

101
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:06,900
- I didn't kill your son!
- [SANDRO SNARLS]

102
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,833
- [BLADE SWISHES]
- [GRUNTS]

103
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:14,833
[GRUNTING]

104
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

105
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:19,833
[GROANING]

106
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,833
Edward, go! Run!

107
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:24,833
Run away, Edward!
Hurry and escape!

108
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:26,800
[GROANING IN PAIN]

109
00:05:27,567 --> 00:05:29,400
[MARTIN] Luna, Jade, Justin!

110
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:31,400
- There's one more piece.
- What is it?

111
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,900
I found it in the music box
that Dad bought me.

112
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:36,533
All this time,
Dad also had a map.

113
00:05:36,533 --> 00:05:37,900
He left us with one.

114
00:05:38,533 --> 00:05:40,700
We can finally
find the treasure.

115
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,667
We can save our siblings now!

116
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:44,533
We will study the map first.

117
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:47,533
Gio, stay here.
Sandro might call us.

118
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,500
- Okay.
- Kiko, will you help me?

119
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:50,667
- Let's go.
- I'll come with you.

120
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,833
I'll stay here with
Gio and Luna.

121
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,433
We'll wait for his call.

122
00:05:54,433 --> 00:05:55,567
Will you be okay?

123
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,667
[RAPHIE] I'll take care
of her, sir.

124
00:05:57,667 --> 00:05:58,667
- Thank you.
- Huh?

125
00:05:58,667 --> 00:05:59,800
What happened?

126
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:01,700
What happened to you?

127
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:04,667
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:08,400
- [KICKS LANDING]
- [GRUNTING]

129
00:06:08,433 --> 00:06:09,600
- Enough!
- [GRUNTS]

130
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:13,933
[BOTH GROANING]

131
00:06:13,933 --> 00:06:15,000
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

132
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:22,100
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GRUNTING, GROANING]

133
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:24,133
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

134
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,100
- [BLADE SWISHES]
- [GRUNTS]

135
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:26,067
Dad!

136
00:06:26,067 --> 00:06:27,367
[THWACK]

137
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:29,833
[GROANING]

138
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:32,967
- [KICKS LANDING]
- [GRUNTING]

139
00:06:32,967 --> 00:06:34,067
[THUDS]

140
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:37,567
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

141
00:06:37,567 --> 00:06:38,667
- [ANDY] Edward!
- [SANDRO GRUNTS]

142
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:40,633
- [THWACKING]
- [ANDY] Edward...

143
00:06:40,633 --> 00:06:41,633
Run!

144
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:43,567
- [THWACKING]
- [GRUNTING]

145
00:06:43,567 --> 00:06:44,633
Run now!

146
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:46,600
- [THWACKING]
- [GRUNTING]

147
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,600
Run now!

148
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,733
- [THWACK]
- [GRUNTS]

149
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:50,133
[GRUNTING, COUGHING]

150
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,667
- [SCREAMS]
- [BLADE SWISHES]

151
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:58,700
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GROANING, SCREAMING]

152
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:02,600
[SANDRO SCREAMING]

153
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,867
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

154
00:07:04,667 --> 00:07:05,633
[GRUNTS]

155
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,167
[THUDS]

156
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:10,533
[SCREAMING, GRUNTING]

157
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:11,533
[THUDS]

158
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:12,667
- Aah!
- [FLESH SQUELCH]

159
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:14,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

160
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:16,133
Edward, run now.

161
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:18,800
Run, hurry!

162
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:21,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,767
[BOTH GRUNTING, GROANING]

164
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:27,833
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

165
00:07:28,867 --> 00:07:30,000
[BODY THUDS]

166
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:36,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:07:36,633 --> 00:07:38,000
Dad!

168
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:43,767
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SCRIBBLING]

169
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:45,967
[JADE] These are four maps,
all with X marks.

170
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,600
That means there are
four treasure locations.

171
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,433
Are we going to all of them?

172
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:54,767
Gio and I agreed that we
shouldn't go to all of them yet.

173
00:07:54,767 --> 00:07:57,633
We need to analyze
these four first.

174
00:07:57,633 --> 00:08:02,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

175
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,033
Do you remember what Papa said,

176
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:06,133
that the treasure
is only at Hotel 88?

177
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:10,167
But these four locations, Kiko,

178
00:08:10,167 --> 00:08:11,933
they are not in Hotel 88.

179
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:18,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:27,733
Wait, I'm going
to try something.

181
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:40,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

182
00:08:56,033 --> 00:08:57,567
[MARTIN] Four locations,

183
00:08:58,300 --> 00:08:59,900
but all of them are outside
the hotel.

184
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,800
But one thing's for sure,
the treasure is in the hotel.

185
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,133
Martin...

186
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:10,867
Kiko...

187
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,167
The point of intersection.

188
00:09:20,067 --> 00:09:22,233
It's on Hotel 88's property.

189
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,067
The treasure is here.

190
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:33,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:36,800
[EDWARD] Dad!

192
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,033
Dad... Dad... Dad!

193
00:09:38,033 --> 00:09:39,100
Dad! [WHIMPERS]

194
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,633
Dad, Dad.

195
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,067
[SOBS] Dad...

196
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:44,100
Dad, please... Dad!
[WHIMPERS]

197
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,033
Dad, wake up. Please.

198
00:09:46,033 --> 00:09:47,733
Dad, Sandro might come back.

199
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,667
Let's go, let's go.

200
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:50,800
Dad... [SOBS]

201
00:09:52,067 --> 00:09:53,200
Dad!

202
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,067
Dad, wake up! [SNIFFLES]

203
00:09:56,933 --> 00:09:58,733
Dad! [SOBS]

204
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:00,833
Dad, there's something
I haven't told you yet.

205
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:02,100
[WHIMPERS]

206
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:04,067
I already forgive you.
[SNIFFLES]

207
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:10,000
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

208
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,600
I already forgive you, Dad.

209
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,633
[SNIFFLES] Let's go.

210
00:10:15,633 --> 00:10:18,733
D-Don't leave me, Dad.
We only have each other.

211
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:25,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:10:26,133 --> 00:10:28,000
[SOBS] Dad!

213
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,200
[SNIFFLES, CRIES]

214
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,867
Dad! [SOBS]

215
00:10:32,867 --> 00:10:34,033
[EDWARD] Dad...

216
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,033
Dad...

217
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:37,200
Dad, wake up!

218
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:40,667
Dad!

219
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,167
Something's wrong.

220
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:47,467
What's wrong?

221
00:10:49,433 --> 00:10:51,000
There are police scattered
all over the island,

222
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,767
but Cheska and Trixie
still haven't been found.

223
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:56,533
Trixie and Cheska are missing.

224
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:58,933
Leon died in the forest.

225
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:04,367
Monette's body was found
by the staff in the mangrove.

226
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:09,367
And Peter was found by Jade.

227
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:16,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,400
And you, Sari,

229
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,800
someone chased you.

230
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:25,933
Sir Gio, what are you
talking about?

231
00:11:29,033 --> 00:11:31,933
What if none of this is a
coincidence here at Hotel 88?

232
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:37,367
It might not be a coincidence
that Sandro was in the forest

233
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:39,400
and Leon and Kiko
were there too.

234
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:42,567
So Sandro could be hiding here?

235
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:46,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:48,967
And maybe Trixie and Cheska
are just here too.

237
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:58,000
- [BOTH PANTING]
- Alright.

238
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,600
- I'm going to count to three.
- Okay.

239
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:02,200
One, two, three!

240
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,900
- [CHAIR CLATTERS]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

241
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:10,000
[BOTH WHIMPERING, GRUNTING]

242
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,200
[GIO] Let's just leave Sari
there for now.

243
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,433
She needs to rest.

244
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:13,633
Let's go through all of this
one by one.

245
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:15,233
[JUSTIN] What are we even
looking for here?

246
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:17,333
Uh, the hotel's blueprint.

247
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,033
Hurry up.

248
00:12:19,033 --> 00:12:20,600
Why do we even need that?

249
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,300
Raphie, if you're going
to tell me

250
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,400
you know every corner
of this hotel,

251
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,600
then fine, we don't need
to look for the blueprint.

252
00:12:26,267 --> 00:12:28,400
Let's just find it,
Raphie, okay?

253
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:31,167
I think I've seen it before.

254
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,067
Monette was the one
organizing it.

255
00:12:33,067 --> 00:12:40,000
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [OBJECT CLATTERING]

256
00:12:45,967 --> 00:12:47,367
Where's the key for this,
Raphie?

257
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:48,400
The key?

258
00:12:48,967 --> 00:12:50,633
I remember it was here.

259
00:12:50,633 --> 00:12:52,500
- [KEY JINGLING]
- Here.

260
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,567
[DRAWER OPENS]

261
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:57,167
[OBJECT CLATTERING]

262
00:12:57,167 --> 00:12:58,167
Check this.

263
00:12:58,167 --> 00:13:05,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:27,300
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:49,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

266
00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:53,133
- Martin, wait.
- We need to hurry, Kiko.

267
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:55,133
This might really be
the treasure.

268
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:57,733
We'll give this to Sandro so
he'll release Trixie and Cheska.

269
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:00,667
I know that, but we still
need to be careful.

270
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:02,133
Jade.

271
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:04,033
Please, don't worry
about me, okay.

272
00:14:04,667 --> 00:14:05,967
[MARTIN] Jade.

273
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:08,400
You can't make me go back
anymore, Martin.

274
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:10,700
I'm with you in the search
for the treasure now.

275
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:24,100
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:26,200
Hey, wait.

277
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:29,467
I think this is it.

278
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:33,733
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:37,633
Place something on the end.

280
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:43,300
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,067
Wait, can you read this?

282
00:14:45,733 --> 00:14:48,233
Gio sells condos, so he knows
these kinds of things.

283
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:52,400
[GIO] This is the basement.

284
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,200
No, this is the basement.

285
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,133
What? This is the very bottom.

286
00:14:56,133 --> 00:14:57,200
No, it's not.

287
00:14:57,567 --> 00:14:59,233
This is the actual lower level.

288
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:01,300
The one with the storage area?

289
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:03,167
Isn't that where you saw a rat?

290
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:06,800
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:08,633
There's a second basement.

292
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:11,433
It's deeper below, and there's
a tunnel out of the hotel.

293
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,767
What if this is where
Sandro is hiding?

294
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:18,567
Raphie and I will go down
to the basement.

295
00:15:18,567 --> 00:15:20,367
Let's go. Let's go!

296
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,667
Sir!

297
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:24,400
I'm tired.

298
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,533
Trixie, you've got this.
Come on, don't give up.

299
00:15:27,533 --> 00:15:30,733
[BOTH GRUNTING]

300
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:32,733
Trixie, we're getting
close to the bomb.

301
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,633
[BOTH GRUNTING]

302
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:37,233
[TIMER BEEPING]

303
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:38,400
Ahh!

304
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:40,533
Oh my God!

305
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:43,533
[CHESKA CRYING]

306
00:15:43,533 --> 00:15:46,467
- Help!
- Help!

307
00:15:46,467 --> 00:15:49,767
[TIMER BEEPING]

308
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:57,600
- [GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BOMB BEEPING]

309
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:00,867
Trixie, don't lose hope.

310
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,133
Hang in there.

311
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:07,567
As long as I'm breathing,

312
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:08,900
I won't give up.

313
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:11,400
As long as we're breathing,
we'll keep fighting.

314
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,767
We'll keep fighting.

315
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:16,367
There's no point, Cheska.
Look what happened.

316
00:16:16,367 --> 00:16:19,300
No, no. Don't talk like that.

317
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:21,700
Don't lose hope, Trixie.

318
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,733
I heard something earlier.

319
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,500
It sounded like someone
opening a door.

320
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,533
Someone's going to save us.

321
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:30,167
- They'll save us.
- [TRIXIE SCOFFS]

322
00:16:30,167 --> 00:16:31,733
- They'll save us.
- Cheska, will you stop?

323
00:16:32,567 --> 00:16:34,867
- Someone's going to save us.
- Cheska!

324
00:16:35,567 --> 00:16:36,867
Someone's going to save us.

325
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:38,867
I don't need
that toxic positivity

326
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:40,433
in the last moments
of my life!

327
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:42,767
So, please stop it!

328
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,367
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

329
00:16:45,367 --> 00:16:46,667
Come on, Trixie.

330
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:52,867
We're about to die here,
and you're still mad at me?

331
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:56,300
We're already here anyway.

332
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:58,733
You said it yourself.
This is the end.

333
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,833
Tell me why you're
so angry with me.

334
00:17:03,933 --> 00:17:06,267
What did I do?

335
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:08,700
Tell me the truth.
Why are you mad at me?

336
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:09,833
Tell me.

337
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:12,600
[SOBS] Please tell me.

338
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,500
[TRIXIE SOBS]

339
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,900
I heard you.

340
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:21,567
I heard you talking to Justin.

341
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,800
[SOBS]

342
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:26,533
I heard you confess
that you have feelings for him.

343
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:30,367
<i> Justin, I like you.</i>

344
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:35,733
<i> You're important to me.</i>

345
00:17:37,867 --> 00:17:39,233
<i> But it's okay.</i>

346
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,800
<i> Come on.</i>

347
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,733
<i> I already know...</i>

348
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:46,733
<i> I'm not your type.</i>

349
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:48,967
<i> I mean, just look at me.</i>

350
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,600
<i>You probably think
we're not a good match.</i>

351
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:53,600
<i> We don't fit.</i>

352
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:55,533
<i> You're up here...</i>

353
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,833
<i> and I'm down here.</i>

354
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:00,267
<i> It's not like that.</i>

355
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,267
<i> It is.</i>

356
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:05,600
<i> It's the truth.</i>

357
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:11,467
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

358
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:29,333
[TRIXIE SOBBING]

359
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,400
You're mad at me...

360
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:34,067
because you're jealous.

361
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:38,633
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

362
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:39,867
I don't know.

363
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:42,833
Tell me the truth.

364
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,733
Yeah.

365
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:47,833
[SOBS]

366
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,833
[CHUCKLES]

367
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:52,933
Yeah.

368
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:56,433
- Trixie...
- I'm sorry.

369
00:18:57,433 --> 00:18:59,400
I get it. I'm sorry.

370
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:05,400
I'm still hung up on my jealousy
even though we're about to die.

371
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,667
I'm sorry.

372
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:10,867
[SOBS] Glad you realize that.

373
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,567
Come on, girl.

374
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:18,533
I only confessed to him
because life is too short.

375
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:21,633
That's why I told him
about my feelings, but...

376
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,600
don't worry.

377
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:26,567
I know we'll never be
more than friends.

378
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,533
<i> So...</i>

379
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:31,367
<i> we're friends?</i>

380
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,667
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

381
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:37,033
<i> Of course.</i>

382
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,533
That's all we'll ever be.

383
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:42,000
And I'm fine with that.

384
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,467
I'm sorry.

385
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:44,667
I'm sorry too.

386
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:46,700
I'm sorry for
getting mad at you.

387
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,767
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

388
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:53,633
- I'm sorry, Cheska.
- It's okay.

389
00:19:53,633 --> 00:19:55,933
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

390
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,333
[BOTH SOBBING]

391
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:02,567
[LUNA] Did you find something?

392
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:05,100
No, Luna. We couldn't open
the door to the basement.

393
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:07,133
There's the tunnel.

394
00:20:07,133 --> 00:20:08,567
That's our only choice.

395
00:20:09,433 --> 00:20:11,667
We need to find out
if Sandro is hiding there.

396
00:20:12,533 --> 00:20:13,733
Regardless if he's there or not,

397
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:15,900
we might find something
that can help us find the girls.

398
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:19,967
What makes you so sure
that Sandro's hiding there?

399
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:21,900
He used to be
my father's contractor.

400
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,500
So he knows the ins and outs
of this hotel.

401
00:20:25,033 --> 00:20:27,467
He might know about
that hidden basement.

402
00:20:27,467 --> 00:20:28,967
What are we waiting for?
Let's go!

403
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:31,633
- I'll go by myself.
- What are you saying?

404
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,700
You can't go alone.
I'm going too.

405
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,967
- Me too.
- I'm going too, Sir Gio.

406
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,933
- I can't stay here either.
- We'll go now.

407
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:40,900
Justin and I will go.
You three stay here.

408
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:42,833
No. I'll go with you.

409
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,900
Gio, I can protect myself.

410
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,400
I can do it.

411
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:51,733
Okay.

412
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:53,800
Sari, Raphie, stay here.

413
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,100
Call Aunt Georgia.

414
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,667
Tell her what we've discovered.

415
00:20:56,667 --> 00:20:57,800
Call the police too.

416
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:58,767
Let's go.

417
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:01,167
- Let's go, Luna.
- Be careful.

418
00:21:01,167 --> 00:21:05,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

419
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:12,733
[MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL]

420
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:13,867
[CHESKA] Trixie!

421
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,433
Cheska...

422
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:24,867
Cheska...

423
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:26,200
Cheska! [LAUGHS]

424
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,533
See?

425
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:30,967
- Oh my god!
- I told you.

426
00:21:30,967 --> 00:21:32,800
- We'll get out of here.
- Oh my god!

427
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,567
We'll get out of here.

428
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:35,933
[SOBBING]

429
00:21:37,767 --> 00:21:39,567
- Come on.
- Let's get out of here.

430
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:44,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

431
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:50,033
This is it.

432
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,233
I'll go in.

433
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:56,700
No.

434
00:21:58,167 --> 00:22:00,267
I already let you come.

435
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:02,033
Now, it's your turn
to listen to me.

436
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:06,633
Justin, stay with
your sister here.

437
00:22:06,633 --> 00:22:07,900
I'm going in too!

438
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,600
It's for Cheska and Trixie!

439
00:22:10,133 --> 00:22:12,533
We can't all go inside.

440
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,833
Okay.

441
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:17,833
Fine.

442
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:20,067
If you see anything inside,
scream, okay?

443
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:21,733
We'll be able to hear you.

444
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:23,733
[LUNA] I'll call Martin.

445
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:30,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

446
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:32,100
[LUNA] Come back alive, okay?

447
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:33,967
Make sure you come back.

448
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:55,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

449
00:23:11,333 --> 00:23:13,000
[GIO EXHALES SHARPLY]

450
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:26,333
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

451
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:45,900
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

452
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,867
- [TRIXIE] Wait!
- [CHESKA] Trixie, hurry up.

453
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:54,133
- There's a chain.
- [CHAIN RATTLING]

454
00:23:54,133 --> 00:23:55,367
It won't come off!

455
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,767
[CHAIN RATTLING]

456
00:23:56,767 --> 00:23:58,000
No!

457
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,833
Trixie!

458
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:02,367
- Help!
- Help!

459
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,700
- [CHAIN RATTLING]
- [TRIXIE CRYING]

460
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:07,133
[CRYING] It won't come off!

461
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:08,800
[CHAIN RATTLING]

462
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,833
Kiko!

463
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:13,833
[TIMER BEEPING]

464
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:16,000
- Help!
- Help!

465
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:23,833
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

466
00:24:38,233 --> 00:24:45,200
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

467
00:24:59,167 --> 00:25:02,400
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

468
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:07,833
This is it.

469
00:25:08,467 --> 00:25:09,833
It's here.

470
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:11,733
[KIKO] Here?

471
00:25:14,367 --> 00:25:16,733
Over there, under the tree.

472
00:25:18,133 --> 00:25:19,267
Okay.

473
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:26,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

474
00:25:28,067 --> 00:25:29,233
Here.

475
00:25:29,233 --> 00:25:30,733
Come on, hurry!

476
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:39,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

477
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:43,967
- [JADE GRUNTS]
- Let's switch.

478
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,967
- Sorry.
- Just dig.

479
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:54,200
[JADE] Hurry.

480
00:25:55,067 --> 00:25:57,567
[TIMER BEEPING]
- Cheska, we can't get this off.

481
00:25:57,567 --> 00:26:00,767
[CHESKA SOBBING]

482
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:08,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

483
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:12,267
- Gio?
- Gio!

484
00:26:12,267 --> 00:26:15,267
Gio, there's a bomb!
There's a bomb!

485
00:26:15,267 --> 00:26:17,167
- Gio, there's a bomb!
- [TRIXIE CRYING]

486
00:26:17,167 --> 00:26:19,200
[CHESKA] Gio, there's a bomb!

487
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:21,167
Gio, help us.

488
00:26:21,167 --> 00:26:23,433
[TIMER BEEPING]

489
00:26:24,967 --> 00:26:31,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

490
00:26:33,367 --> 00:26:35,233
[CHESKA AND TRIXIE CRYING]

491
00:26:35,233 --> 00:26:36,833
Gio, we're not going to make it!

492
00:26:36,833 --> 00:26:38,300
We're not going to make it!

493
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,833
- We're not going to make it!
- We're not going to make it!

494
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:43,233
[TIMER BEEPING]

495
00:26:45,333 --> 00:26:46,633
<i> What's this?</i>

496
00:26:46,633 --> 00:26:48,000
<i> What was that?</i>

497
00:26:48,933 --> 00:26:50,033
<i> Argh!</i>

498
00:26:54,233 --> 00:26:56,933
<i> Save yourself!</i>

499
00:26:56,933 --> 00:27:00,467
<i>We're all going to die,
just make it one less!</i>

500
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,867
<i>- Gio!
- Gio, please!</i>

501
00:27:04,233 --> 00:27:07,567
[EXPLOSION]

502
00:27:07,567 --> 00:27:08,933
<i> Ahh!</i>

503
00:27:10,233 --> 00:27:12,167
<i> Trixie! Cheska!</i>

504
00:27:12,167 --> 00:27:13,200
<i> Gio!</i>
